19#include "DMECB.h"
20
21namespace ZXing {
22namespace DataMatrix {
23
24/**
25* The Version object encapsulates attributes about a particular
26* size Data Matrix Code.
27*
28* @author bbrown@google.com (Brian Brown)
29*/
30class Version
31{
32public:
33 int versionNumber() const {
34 return _versionNumber;
35 }
36
37 int symbolSizeRows() const {
38 return _symbolSizeRows;
39 }
40
41 int symbolSizeColumns() const {
42 return _symbolSizeColumns;
43 }
44
45 int dataRegionSizeRows() const {
46 return _dataRegionSizeRows;
47 }
48
49 int dataRegionSizeColumns() const {
50 return _dataRegionSizeColumns;
51 }
52
53 int totalCodewords() const {
54 return _ecBlocks.totalDataCodewords();
55 }
56
57 const ECBlocks& ecBlocks() const {
58 return _ecBlocks;
59 }
60
61 /**
62 * <p>Deduces version information from Data Matrix dimensions.</p>
63 *
64 * @param numRows Number of rows in modules
65 * @param numColumns Number of columns in modules
66 * @return Version for a Data Matrix Code of those dimensions
67 * @throws FormatException if dimensions do correspond to a valid Data Matrix size
68 */
69 static const Version* VersionForDimensions(int numRows, int numColumns);
70
71private:
72 int _versionNumber;
73 int _symbolSizeRows;
74 int _symbolSizeColumns;
75 int _dataRegionSizeRows;
76 int _dataRegionSizeColumns;
77 ECBlocks _ecBlocks;
78
79 Version(int versionNumber, int symbolSizeRows, int symbolSizeColumns, int dataRegionSizeRows, int dataRegionSizeColumns, const ECBlocks& ecBlocks);
80};
81
82} // DataMatrix
83} // ZXing
